<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1>Surf Ed</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The Ocean Grove Surf Ed program is a perfect introduction to surf lifesaving activities for children aged 7 to 12. Surf awareness and beach safety, as well as developing new skills and making new friends. At Surf Ed the beach is the classroom. The program aims to build confidence in the water and on the beach by learning new skills such as body surfing, beach sprints, wading, dolphin-diving and board padding. Activities are conducted by qualified instructors.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Member aged 7-13 are automatically enrolled in Surf Ed. You can just turn up for the first session. Attendees are required to wear an OGSLSC competition cap. These can be purchased at surf ed sessions for $20 cash and Eftpos accepted.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Surf Ed runs for six sessions in the evening from late December to early January each year. At the first Surf Ed session your child will complete a preliminary swim assessment by a qualified assessor from the Club. This is to ensure that adequate water safety is provided for all Surf Ed participants based on their abilities. <br><a href="http://www."><em>For Surf Ed dates click here.</em></a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1>Surf Sports</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The OGSLSC Surf Sport program is for those children looking to extend their surf lifesaving skills. The Surf Sport program is a fantastic way to keep fit, make new friends and get to the beach every weekend. Surf Sport Nippers are expected to also participate in Surf Ed are encouraged to represent the club at local and state carnivals. Before starting training, all Surf Sport Nippers need to complete and return the Swim Proficiency Form to Darren Ball or to <a href="mailto:admin@oceangroveslsc.asn.au">admin@oceangroveslsc.asn.au</a> . Surf Sport children may choose to attend all, a couple or no  carnivals throughout the season. Entry fees must be paid prior to the carnival.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Fees and Additional Costs</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>$30 Surf Sport Levy applies to all children who train and/or compete in carnivals.</li><li>$50 Foam board Levy (applicable to those who use club boards).</li><li>$35 Nippers Rash Vest which must be worn during training. Can be purchased from the uniform shop.</li><li>$20 Club Competition Cap is require for competitions. Available for purchase at club and first couple of Surf Ed programs.</li><li>$32 Standard Carnival.</li><li>$48 State Championships including Enduros, IRB and pool.</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Training<br>Visitors from other clubs are welcome to join in with OGSLSC training sessions, please first read the attached visitor's code of conduct and contact junior activities manager Damen Ball on <strong>0413600344</strong>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Surf Sport Nippers train at main beach, October to March, training sessions are Fridays 5.30 pm - 6.30 pm and Sundays 10 am -11.30 am. It's no problem if you can't attend all sessions.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Training consists of water activities such as boards, swimming and wading as well as beach activities such as sprints, flags and relays.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Surf Sport Nippers are encouraged to represent the OGSLSC at various carnivals during the summer season which is a great way for nippers to test their skills against other nippers, as well as have a lot of fun, juniors carnival dates are listed on the nippers calendar.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Swimming Requirements & pre-season training<br>As a lead into the Surf Sport season the club runs 4 training sessions at Ocean Grove Pool (BASC) in August. New members are welcome and encouraged to join these training sessions as they provide an excellent introduction to Surf Sport. Nippers are required to pay pool entry. If you are new to the club, please join online following the steps provided on our <a href="https://oceangroveslsccom.wordpress.com/how-to-join/">how to join</a> page.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>For those who were unable to attend the August pool sessions, assessments will be done at the first Surf Sport session your child attends. The swim requiremnets for Surf Sport Nippers are as follows:<br></p>
